WEBVTT

00:01.268 --> 00:03.335
(silence)

00:10.845 --> 00:13.579
(ominous music)

00:58.025 --> 01:01.260
(children chattering)

01:12.706 --> 01:14.773
(saw whirring)

01:14.775 --> 01:17.576
(hammer banging)

01:18.446 --> 01:21.413
(sandpaper scraping)

01:21.415 --> 01:24.450
(brushing)

01:24.452 --> 01:27.286
(birds chirping)

01:39.133 --> 01:41.700
(dog barking)

01:58.619 --> 02:01.320
(phone ringing)

02:11.198 --> 02:14.032
(engine revving)

02:17.371 --> 02:18.837
- Overnight, you know
what I mean?

02:18.839 --> 02:19.771
So, you got it?

02:19.773 --> 02:21.140
- Okay.
- Okay, thanks.

02:25.679 --> 02:27.379
- Hello, handsome.

02:27.381 --> 02:29.348
- No public displays
of affection at school.

02:29.350 --> 02:31.250
- Oh, but you know
I'm a bad girl.

02:32.753 --> 02:33.719
- How bad?

02:33.721 --> 02:35.220
- So bad.

02:35.222 --> 02:36.321
- Really bad?

02:36.323 --> 02:37.256
- Very, very bad.

02:38.359 --> 02:39.691
- Say something sexy.

02:40.494 --> 02:43.328
- I finished unpacking
the last box today.

02:43.330 --> 02:45.797
We're completely moved in.

02:45.799 --> 02:47.399
- Oh, my god, I'm so turned on
right now.

02:47.401 --> 02:48.233
(laughing)

02:48.235 --> 02:49.134
It only took eight months.

02:49.136 --> 02:51.904
- But it's done, we're home.

02:53.407 --> 02:55.007
Only a few things left to do.

02:55.009 --> 02:56.308
- Oh, there's a few things
left, what few things?

02:56.310 --> 03:00.946
- It's nothing, you promised
me a door for the hall closet.

03:00.948 --> 03:02.665
- Oh, yeah.

03:02.666 --> 03:04.383
- And we need curtains
for the bedroom.

03:04.385 --> 03:07.252
And a rug for the guest room.

03:07.254 --> 03:08.587
- And that's it?

03:08.589 --> 03:09.655
- That's it.

03:10.791 --> 03:11.723
For now.

03:11.725 --> 03:13.258
(laughing)

03:13.260 --> 03:15.194
You knew what I was when you
married me.

03:15.196 --> 03:17.196
(groaning)

03:17.198 --> 03:18.764
Jesus, Ma, it's the principal.

03:18.766 --> 03:20.399
(laughing)

03:20.401 --> 03:22.000
- Hi.
- Hi.

03:22.002 --> 03:23.602
Hello, Ms. Eden.

03:23.604 --> 03:25.671
- Hi, Ms. Raleigh, I'm
just here to pick up Kane

03:25.673 --> 03:27.839
and I'll quit distracting
your foreman.

03:27.841 --> 03:29.408
I must say, I think
he's doing a great job.

03:29.410 --> 03:31.443
- Ah, the work is above average.

03:31.445 --> 03:33.912
Although, we've been up
against the clock, haven't we?

03:33.914 --> 03:35.847
- Yes and I do need
to get back to work.

03:35.849 --> 03:37.182
- Oh, right.
- We gotta pour

03:37.184 --> 03:38.717
that concrete,
it's gonna set overnight.

03:38.719 --> 03:39.618
- Okay.

03:39.620 --> 03:40.485
- Back to the salt mine.

03:40.487 --> 03:41.853
- Okay, see you tonight.

03:41.855 --> 03:42.754
Poppy seed chicken.

03:42.756 --> 03:44.289
- Oh, I'm there.
- Okay.

03:44.291 --> 03:45.857
- And I do need to go get Kane,

03:45.859 --> 03:46.992
but I wanna thank you again

03:46.994 --> 03:49.394
for this opportunity
for my family.

03:49.396 --> 03:52.164
If it weren't for you and
the board allowing Red

03:52.166 --> 03:57.135
to trade for and the school
is gonna be so great.

03:59.540 --> 04:03.408
We could never do this right
now without this arrangement.

04:03.410 --> 04:05.777
- Kane is continuing to
assimilate here.

04:06.580 --> 04:11.016
It's more, than the teachers
would like, but I think

04:11.018 --> 04:13.986
there's a great chance,
that eventually

04:13.988 --> 04:15.487
he'll be a good fit here.

04:16.890 --> 04:18.589
- Well, thank you, thank you.

04:23.664 --> 04:27.332
(children whispering)

04:27.334 --> 04:29.668
(laughing)

04:36.076 --> 04:38.110
Hey, buddy, ready to go?

04:39.013 --> 04:41.980
Look what I found in a flee
market today.

04:41.982 --> 04:44.750
Remember, your favorite
one we lost in the move.

04:44.752 --> 04:46.118
- My car.

04:46.120 --> 04:47.052
- One just like it.

04:47.054 --> 04:48.553
- Thanks, mom.

04:48.555 --> 04:51.657
- You're so welcome, honey,
ready to go?

04:51.659 --> 04:53.125
- Yeah, let's go.

04:54.962 --> 04:57.996
- I'm so sorry, buddy,
I know it's hard,

04:58.999 --> 05:01.166
but we have to keep trying.

05:01.168 --> 05:04.269
- I hate this school, I
hate it, kids don't like me,

05:04.271 --> 05:07.572
the teachers are mean, I get
in trouble all day for nothing,

05:07.574 --> 05:09.608
Ms. Raleigh won't let me
have my car in the class,

05:09.610 --> 05:10.742
they hate me here.

05:10.744 --> 05:12.844
- They don't hate you,
they don't, Kane,

05:12.846 --> 05:14.413
they just don't know you yet.

05:14.415 --> 05:15.981
- I don't wanna
go to school here.

05:15.983 --> 05:17.549
- Well, that's not
up for discussion.

05:17.551 --> 05:19.217
- I don't wanna
go to school here.

05:19.219 --> 05:20.118
- Kane,

05:21.655 --> 05:23.689
when we moved here we thought
there would be more work

05:23.691 --> 05:25.991
for your daddy, but it was
slower, than we wanted and,

05:25.993 --> 05:29.261
you know, we wanna put
you in the best school

05:29.263 --> 05:33.131
we possibly can, you know
what Dr. Timmon said.

05:33.133 --> 05:36.835
- I have to go to a special
school, where they can help me,

05:36.837 --> 05:38.670
because my brain works
different.

05:38.672 --> 05:41.239
- That's right and you
don't have to be embarrassed

05:41.241 --> 05:42.274
about that, honey.

05:43.310 --> 05:46.545
We want the very best for you.

05:48.582 --> 05:52.117
And daddy is trading
work for you to be able

05:52.119 --> 05:53.819
to go to this special school.

05:55.356 --> 05:58.523
You know, we can't afford
it any other way, remember?

05:58.525 --> 06:01.043
- I remember.

06:01.044 --> 06:03.562
- Okay, so as long as daddy
is working for this school,

06:03.564 --> 06:07.399
this is your school, okay?

06:07.401 --> 06:08.967
- Okay.

06:08.969 --> 06:11.837
- Kane is good, he told
me to hug the phone,

06:11.839 --> 06:12.938
when you called.

06:13.841 --> 06:17.542
Yeah, Red is great,
the school job has been

06:17.544 --> 06:21.613
great word of mouth, lots of
compliments from the parents

06:21.615 --> 06:22.581
about the work.

06:24.451 --> 06:25.650
Well and you know,
they all have money

06:25.652 --> 06:26.585
or they'd be in a different
school, so.

06:26.587 --> 06:27.753
(doorbell ringing)

06:27.755 --> 06:31.456
Oh, hey, mom, I need
to go, I have a guest.

06:31.458 --> 06:34.059
Okay, I love you, okay, bye.

06:35.195 --> 06:37.496
(doorbell ringing)

06:37.498 --> 06:38.397
Coming.

06:41.769 --> 06:45.070
(hinges creaking)

06:45.072 --> 06:46.605
- Hi, Evelyn.

06:46.607 --> 06:47.806
- [Evelyn] Come inside.

06:51.912 --> 06:54.146
These swords always
freak me out.

06:54.148 --> 06:57.816
- Oh, they don't mean anything.

06:57.818 --> 06:59.384
- I know.

06:59.386 --> 07:00.952
- Not on their own.

07:00.954 --> 07:03.021
- I know, it's just a knee
jerk reaction.

07:15.269 --> 07:16.935
- It's all good.

07:18.038 --> 07:22.140
It about Red, your husband.

07:23.444 --> 07:28.513
More opportunities, more
freedom, more money.

07:29.383 --> 07:30.882
- Well, that's all good news.

07:32.186 --> 07:34.286
- Now, it's on you.

07:38.091 --> 07:40.826
(ominous music)

07:44.398 --> 07:46.465
- [Evelyn] What is this?

07:48.135 --> 07:53.205
- It's a Pisces, a portal
sending for you here an opening.

07:55.342 --> 07:58.844
- We've talked about starting
a new internet business

07:58.846 --> 08:00.412
to sell some of my hobby work.

08:01.448 --> 08:06.218
- Maybe, this is bigger.

08:07.221 --> 08:08.119
It is,

08:09.723 --> 08:10.989
you should be careful.

08:11.892 --> 08:12.791
- It's bad?

08:14.828 --> 08:19.531
- Anytime you open a new
door, you can never be sure

08:19.533 --> 08:24.202
what's on the other side of
the wall until you're there.

08:25.038 --> 08:29.474
It means this can
be good, it's dangerous.

08:30.410 --> 08:33.445
- You think this is dangerous?

08:34.248 --> 08:37.883
- I don't know, you
should be cautious,

08:37.885 --> 08:38.850
when you open...

08:38.852 --> 08:41.820
(door slamming)

08:41.822 --> 08:43.355
- Kane, whatever happened?

08:45.092 --> 08:46.391
- Go to your room.

08:46.392 --> 08:47.691
- They wouldn't stop
laughing at me, mom.

08:47.694 --> 08:49.027
- Kane.

08:49.029 --> 08:51.062
- Do what your dad
says, we'll talk later.

08:52.266 --> 08:54.299
- Juryah, good to see you.

08:54.301 --> 08:55.834
- Hello.

08:55.836 --> 08:56.735
- Excuse me.

08:56.737 --> 08:59.337
Really, the third visit
from the psychic?

08:59.339 --> 09:00.705
- I wanted him to
bless the house,

09:00.707 --> 09:02.741
now that we're finally
unpacked and he doesn't need

09:02.743 --> 09:04.576
to be called a
psychic, he's an augur.

09:04.578 --> 09:06.411
- He's a psychic
you found on Craigslist.

09:06.413 --> 09:08.980
- Humor me, I wanted the house
blessed.

09:08.982 --> 09:10.715
- Craigslist didn't
have priests?

09:13.587 --> 09:16.121
I can't believe
I'm gonna say this.

09:16.123 --> 09:17.055
- Can he come back later?

09:17.057 --> 09:18.056
- Can he come back later?

09:18.058 --> 09:18.957
- Yes.

09:20.193 --> 09:23.128
- Alright, I took the
rest of the afternoon off

09:23.130 --> 09:25.263
to deal with this,
I'm gonna go shower.

09:29.236 --> 09:33.405
- Juryah, would you mind
coming back for the blessing

09:33.407 --> 09:34.406
next week?

09:35.409 --> 09:38.443
- Of course,
of course, next week.

09:41.615 --> 09:42.647
- So what happened?

09:44.685 --> 09:48.119
- He said, at lunch time all
these kids were laughing at him

09:48.121 --> 09:50.789
and he has to sit down and
they kept making fun of him

09:50.791 --> 09:53.291
and finally he hit one and
another kid jumped on him,

09:53.293 --> 09:55.860
and then the teachers
had to pull em apart.

09:55.862 --> 09:58.697
And then Raleigh calls me
in along with the councilor

09:58.699 --> 10:01.066
and sends him home for the day,
and now he's got a three day

10:01.068 --> 10:02.300
in-school suspension.

10:03.136 --> 10:04.703
- So what do we do now, Red.

10:04.705 --> 10:06.137
- I don't know, these
other kids are starting it.

10:06.139 --> 10:08.740
- No, no, he can't
hit other kids.

10:08.742 --> 10:10.675
- Well, he's gotta
stand up for himself.

10:10.677 --> 10:12.110
If these other kids are gonna--

10:12.112 --> 10:14.479
- No, he can't hit
other kids, he can't,

10:14.481 --> 10:16.648
it's not the way
the world works.

10:16.650 --> 10:18.316
- It is the way the world works.

10:19.252 --> 10:21.886
But he can't hit other
kids and stay at the school

10:22.723 --> 10:24.789
and we need this school.

10:26.627 --> 10:28.593
- So what do we do now?

10:31.865 --> 10:36.935
So, no video games, no
movies, no TV, no apps, okay?

10:37.371 --> 10:38.436
- For how long?

10:38.438 --> 10:40.171
- [Evelyn] We're gonna
start with two weeks.

10:40.173 --> 10:42.073
- That's forever.

10:42.075 --> 10:44.192
- [Red] You'll live.

10:44.193 --> 10:46.310
- And if we don't see
improvement, it could be longer.

10:46.313 --> 10:48.113
- That's not fair.

10:48.114 --> 10:49.914
- You know what's not fair
is us making the sacrifices,

10:49.916 --> 10:51.516
that we're making for
you to go to that school

10:51.518 --> 10:53.918
and then you not following
simple rules.

10:53.920 --> 10:57.022
- So you're grounded, it's
gonna be homework and chores,

10:57.024 --> 11:01.559
you can still play outside and
draw and play with your cars,

11:01.561 --> 11:03.561
but your councilor and
the principal think,

11:03.563 --> 11:06.531
that too much screen time
is having a negative effect.

11:06.533 --> 11:08.333
- Can I have my
cars in class, just once?

11:08.335 --> 11:10.235
- No, buddy, no cars in class.

11:11.972 --> 11:13.905
We do have some
good news, though.

11:14.808 --> 11:16.408
- You shouldn't think
of this as a reward,

11:16.410 --> 11:17.709
because you are grounded.

11:19.246 --> 11:21.479
- The councilor thinks you need
to spend some time outside,

11:21.481 --> 11:25.216
burn off some energy, so we're
gonna go for a hike tomorrow.

11:25.218 --> 11:26.718
- A hike, in the woods?

11:26.720 --> 11:30.088
- Yeah, we're gonna go to the
state park and take a hike,

11:30.090 --> 11:31.923
and have a picnic on--

11:31.925 --> 11:33.825
- Can I bring my binoculars,

11:33.827 --> 11:35.126
can I bring my magnifying glass?

11:35.128 --> 11:36.728
- Yeah, you can bring whatever
you want,

11:36.730 --> 11:38.897
load up your backpack, but
we can't get too excited,

11:38.899 --> 11:40.031
we gotta go to sleep tonight.

11:40.033 --> 11:42.417
- I can't wait, I can't
wait, I can't wait.

11:42.418 --> 11:44.802
- Okay, okay, get
under the covers,

11:44.805 --> 11:46.604
you need to get some
sleep, if you're gonna run

11:46.606 --> 11:48.173
all over the forest tomorrow.

11:49.409 --> 11:50.709
- Goodnight, buddy.

11:50.711 --> 11:51.676
- Goodnight, baby.

11:52.546 --> 11:55.046
(hinges creaking)

11:55.048 --> 11:57.682
- Get up, get up, get up,
get up, get up, get up.

11:57.684 --> 11:59.117
- Looks who's up.
- Get up, get up, get up!

11:59.119 --> 12:03.521
- Usually, your mom has to drag
you out of bed by the ears.

12:04.524 --> 12:05.523
- I'll start breakfast,

12:05.525 --> 12:07.258
if you could make
sandwiches for lunch.

12:07.260 --> 12:10.729
- I need big pieces of bread
to make a king sandwich

12:10.731 --> 12:11.896
for the bears.

12:11.898 --> 12:12.764
- There's bears?

12:12.766 --> 12:14.032
- [Evelyn] There aren't any
bears.

12:14.034 --> 12:15.467
- There's definitely bears,
there's definitely bears

12:17.537 --> 12:19.104
and they're gonna get you.

12:19.106 --> 12:21.840
(ominous music)

12:30.784 --> 12:33.284
No way.

12:33.286 --> 12:34.385
- They'll look fantastic.

12:34.387 --> 12:36.821
- (laughs) No, they would not.

12:36.823 --> 12:40.024
- Come on, beaded curtains
are huge right now.

12:40.026 --> 12:41.526
- Sure they are (laughs).

12:41.528 --> 12:44.829
- What , we need something
at the end of the hall.

12:44.831 --> 12:47.832
That rent house,
it looks like a condo.

12:50.771 --> 12:52.237
- That's what was available.

12:52.239 --> 12:53.404
- I'm not complaining.

12:55.175 --> 12:58.877
I'm grateful we were
able to find something.

12:58.879 --> 13:01.679
(birds chirping)

13:09.156 --> 13:12.290
- We're ready to
have the talk again.

13:13.360 --> 13:14.259
- About?

13:16.530 --> 13:17.595
- What if it helped?

13:19.900 --> 13:22.066
- I'm not stuffing him full of
pills, Red.

13:23.270 --> 13:26.437
- I'm not talking about
pouring meds down his neck,

13:26.439 --> 13:28.406
don't frame it
like that, I'm just,

13:31.011 --> 13:36.080
I'm just asking, if we need
to carefully and thoroughly--

13:36.416 --> 13:37.615
- It's a quick fix.

13:39.186 --> 13:44.255
The side effects, the months
it takes to dial in the dosage.

13:44.457 --> 13:48.660
- I just wanna make sure, that
we are open to every option,

13:48.662 --> 13:49.928
that might help him.

13:49.930 --> 13:50.762
- I'm open.

13:50.764 --> 13:52.163
(piano music)

13:52.165 --> 13:54.032
I never stopped researching.

13:55.268 --> 13:58.369
I'm not hung up on vaccines,
I'm not that person.

14:00.874 --> 14:05.043
I just haven't seen anything,
that makes me believe

14:05.045 --> 14:07.245
a pill is the answer.

14:07.247 --> 14:10.248
(piano music)

14:10.250 --> 14:13.518
(birds chirping)

14:13.520 --> 14:14.485
- Okay.

14:14.487 --> 14:15.920
- Okay.

14:15.922 --> 14:18.489
(piano music)

14:27.067 --> 14:28.099
- What is it?

14:32.806 --> 14:37.141
- Kane, come here, come here,
come here, be quiet, be quiet.

14:37.143 --> 14:38.877
- [Kane] What is it?

14:40.580 --> 14:43.381
- I think it might
be a bear, a bear!

14:45.552 --> 14:47.886
(laughing)

14:56.730 --> 14:58.997
I got you a little something.

14:58.999 --> 15:00.498
- For?

15:00.500 --> 15:05.536
- For being great, about the
move and all the sacrifices

15:05.872 --> 15:07.405
you're making for your family.

15:08.441 --> 15:10.208
I know the house isn't
what you had envisioned,

15:10.210 --> 15:12.210
when we made
our fresh start, but--

15:12.212 --> 15:15.146
- Is it a sack of
diamonds. Is it diamonds,

15:15.148 --> 15:17.749
did you get me a potato
sack full of diamonds.

15:17.751 --> 15:19.517
- Well, it's not in a sack.

15:30.730 --> 15:32.397
- My own online store.

15:32.399 --> 15:35.433
- I bought the URL and I
set up a simple website,

15:35.435 --> 15:37.969
it connects to all the crafty
sites.

15:37.971 --> 15:39.371
- My God.

15:39.372 --> 15:40.772
- I mean it's not finished,
but it'll take payments

15:40.774 --> 15:41.940
and everything.

15:41.942 --> 15:42.840
- This,

15:44.811 --> 15:46.644
this is so great.

15:46.646 --> 15:47.512
- Do you like it?

15:47.514 --> 15:49.881
- Yes, thank you, thank you.

15:52.085 --> 15:54.118
- I wish I could do more.

15:54.120 --> 15:56.955
(birds chirping)

16:05.432 --> 16:06.764
- Where is Kane?

16:06.766 --> 16:09.500
(ominous music)

16:20.180 --> 16:21.212
- It's door.

16:21.214 --> 16:24.415
- I see it's a door,
it's a really cool door.

16:25.218 --> 16:26.117
- Cool.

16:27.320 --> 16:30.088
- Yes, vintage, weathered.

16:31.391 --> 16:32.590
- It's creepy.

16:34.060 --> 16:35.326
- Every antique has a story

16:35.328 --> 16:36.828
and you always
assume it's creepy.

16:36.830 --> 16:39.564
- This is creepy, what,
someone left a door out here?

16:39.566 --> 16:41.966
- I don't know, people dump
treasures all the time,

16:41.968 --> 16:44.936
look, they even left the key.

16:44.938 --> 16:47.238
It's just waiting for us.

16:48.375 --> 16:50.074
All it needs is to be refinished

16:50.076 --> 16:51.642
with a little love and care.

16:52.946 --> 16:54.546
- Are you serious?

16:54.547 --> 16:56.147
- Yeah, you see creepy,
I see potential, Red,

16:56.149 --> 16:58.816
it even looks, like it's the
right size.

16:58.818 --> 17:02.053
- I love your creative
vision, but I do not see it.

17:02.055 --> 17:05.022
- I always see the potential,
it's why I married you.

17:05.959 --> 17:10.028
Look, it's not a beaded curtain
and if the house is finished

17:10.030 --> 17:11.996
then I can focus my full
attention on getting

17:11.998 --> 17:13.664
the online store up and running.

17:16.435 --> 17:19.470
- I'll go get the truck,
I'm not hauling that thing.

17:19.472 --> 17:21.772
- You're the bestest,
strongest husband ever.

17:24.944 --> 17:27.244
(laughing)

17:30.583 --> 17:33.418
(sander buzzing)

17:49.102 --> 17:50.735
- Thank you, honey.

17:54.174 --> 17:55.239
Well poured.

18:10.957 --> 18:13.691
(drill buzzing)

18:25.538 --> 18:27.371
Works and everything.

18:54.300 --> 18:57.101
(hinge creaking)

19:11.117 --> 19:13.851
(ominous music)

19:20.793 --> 19:24.028
(children chattering)

19:45.618 --> 19:48.920
Hey, you have a
late night snack?

19:48.922 --> 19:50.021
- No, not me.

19:50.023 --> 19:53.324
- Oh, he's sleep walking again.

19:53.326 --> 19:54.659
- [Red] And sleep eating?

19:54.661 --> 19:57.562
- Didn't even bother heating
it up, just munched on it cold.

19:57.564 --> 20:00.598
- I got to go to work early to
make up

20:00.600 --> 20:02.967
for that half day on Friday,
can you take Kane to school?

20:02.969 --> 20:05.303
- Sure, sure, you
don't want any bacon?

20:05.305 --> 20:06.437
- Nah.

20:06.439 --> 20:07.638
- Or a waffle?

20:08.741 --> 20:11.142
- No, I'm good, love you.

20:11.144 --> 20:12.210
- Love you too.

20:17.383 --> 20:19.383
- I'm so sleepy.

20:19.384 --> 20:21.384
- Yeah, I figured, do you
remember getting up last night?

20:21.387 --> 20:23.704
- [Kane] No.

20:23.705 --> 20:26.022
- Well, eat fast,
we're gonna be late.

20:26.025 --> 20:28.159
Oh, Kane, you've
got to comb your hair.

20:30.230 --> 20:31.629
- We're out of milk.

20:31.631 --> 20:34.298
- I'll pick some up after
I take you to school, eat.

20:44.010 --> 20:46.310
Kane, did you leave some
food in the jacket pocket

20:46.312 --> 20:48.045
or something, the closet reeks.

20:48.047 --> 20:49.981
- No.

20:49.982 --> 20:51.916
- Well, then it's shoes, gross,
you done?

20:53.953 --> 20:55.419
Get your backpack, let's go.

21:04.130 --> 21:06.864
(ominous music)

21:13.773 --> 21:18.843
Kane, oh, I'm gonna
skin you alive, oh, God.

21:23.616 --> 21:24.582
- Yes, yes.

21:25.752 --> 21:27.618
- Kane swears he didn't do it.

21:28.821 --> 21:31.088
- Well, maybe they
crawled in from the vent.

21:32.125 --> 21:37.194
- Red, it was full, full,
they didn't climb in there.

21:40.233 --> 21:44.001
- I'll talk to him, but maybe
you want me to put some traps

21:44.003 --> 21:45.169
in there just in case?

21:46.472 --> 21:50.074
- Sure, put some traps in there,
see if they catch anything.

21:50.076 --> 21:53.878
- [Announcer] 35, 40, what
a block, 45, still going--

21:53.880 --> 21:55.613
- And talk to Kane.

21:55.615 --> 21:56.714
- Yeah, what?

21:56.716 --> 21:59.417
- [Announcer] This game is
really getting.

21:59.419 --> 22:02.053
(horror music)

22:03.990 --> 22:07.258
- I can't sleep,
I'm having bad dreams.

22:08.094 --> 22:09.060
- You okay?

22:09.062 --> 22:10.795
- Yeah, it's nothing, I just.

22:13.499 --> 22:16.133
- I'm walking through a
house with lots of rooms

22:16.135 --> 22:17.268
and it's following me.

22:17.270 --> 22:18.903
- It?

22:18.905 --> 22:20.304
- The bad thing.

22:22.175 --> 22:24.342
- What's the bad thing?

22:24.343 --> 22:26.510
- I don't know, it's just a
bad thing, it wants to get me.

22:26.512 --> 22:27.712
- A monster?

22:28.881 --> 22:30.014
- You okay, buddy?

22:31.351 --> 22:33.384
You know, we're
right across the hall,

22:33.386 --> 22:34.785
I'm not gonna let anything
happen to you.

22:34.787 --> 22:35.820
- I know.

22:37.690 --> 22:41.058
- You know, there's no such
thing as monster, right?

22:41.060 --> 22:41.892
- Yeah.

22:41.894 --> 22:43.060
- [Evelyn] They aren't real.

22:43.062 --> 22:46.497
- I don't believe in monsters,
but I'm scared of them.

22:46.499 --> 22:48.866
- Well, can you think of happy
things,

22:48.868 --> 22:53.938
like taking a hike or a cool
bug, or driving a fast car?

22:56.642 --> 22:59.343
- I try to think of happy
things, but every time I close

22:59.345 --> 23:01.345
my eyes I see the bad thing.

23:02.749 --> 23:05.216
- Well, can you think of
anything, that can make you
think

23:05.218 --> 23:06.751
of good things?

23:06.753 --> 23:07.752
- Grandma's prayer.

23:08.888 --> 23:09.787
- Okay.

23:09.789 --> 23:15.659
Our father, who art in
heaven, hallowed be thy name,

23:16.729 --> 23:21.499
thy kingdom come, thy
will be done, on earth,

23:21.501 --> 23:26.470
as it is in heaven, give
us this day our daily bread

23:27.306 --> 23:30.708
and forgive us our sins,
as we forgive those,

23:30.710 --> 23:32.476
who sin against us.

23:34.247 --> 23:38.315
And lead us not into temptation,
but deliver us from evil,

23:39.218 --> 23:44.288
for thine is the kingdom,
and the power, and the glory,

23:44.424 --> 23:46.157
forever and ever.

23:46.159 --> 23:49.393
(horror violin music)

23:53.833 --> 23:54.732
Amen.

24:07.613 --> 24:11.315
(children chattering)

24:11.317 --> 24:13.617
(knocking)

24:15.688 --> 24:19.590
- Hi, this is no longer a safe
place,

24:19.592 --> 24:21.559
this house has changed.

24:22.562 --> 24:23.994
- Come inside.

24:23.996 --> 24:24.895
- Thank you.

24:27.567 --> 24:28.466
- What's wrong?

24:29.402 --> 24:32.970
- I'm not sure, but
this house, it unclean,

24:32.972 --> 24:35.039
it afflicted by spirits.

24:36.108 --> 24:41.145
Dark phantoms haunted by
the trinity of the veil.

24:42.782 --> 24:47.852
- My house is haunted, no,
the evil has an invitation,

24:49.121 --> 24:51.388
someone brought it here.

24:52.792 --> 24:55.759
- What, we invited an evil
spirit?

24:55.761 --> 25:00.831
Okay, I believe in psychic
ability and the tarot,

25:02.602 --> 25:05.269
but ghosts, isn't it a little?

25:05.271 --> 25:09.707
- You cannot believe in
only half of the next world.

25:11.377 --> 25:16.380
I sense malice
from the other side.

25:17.450 --> 25:18.782
- Okay.

25:18.784 --> 25:21.085
- We must bless this house.

25:22.889 --> 25:25.623
(ominous music)

26:39.265 --> 26:41.966
Where did you get this door?

26:42.868 --> 26:45.603
(ominous music)

27:17.670 --> 27:19.837
Okay, all done.

27:26.879 --> 27:30.214
Understand, there are no
guarantees.

27:30.216 --> 27:32.516
- I understand, yeah.

27:32.518 --> 27:36.186
- You should remove
this door, burn it.

27:37.490 --> 27:39.423
- Okay, I'll talk to Red.

27:40.426 --> 27:43.494
- Be careful,
be careful with things

27:43.496 --> 27:45.929
you bring into this house.

27:52.405 --> 27:54.505
- Second one,
what is with these bits.

27:54.507 --> 27:55.839
- Not coming out?

27:55.841 --> 27:58.409
- No, it won't budge
and these pins,

27:58.411 --> 28:00.310
they're stuck in here,
I can't knock them out.

28:00.312 --> 28:02.513
- Well, how are we
gonna get it out then?

28:02.515 --> 28:04.048
- I don't know, sledge hammer?

28:05.084 --> 28:06.850
Honey, this isn't
a one night job.

28:07.720 --> 28:09.019
- But I want it gone.

28:15.594 --> 28:18.328
- You begged for this
door and now one word

28:18.330 --> 28:20.297
from your psychic friend, who,
by the way,

28:20.299 --> 28:22.900
may have visited here today
and you wanna pull it?

28:24.203 --> 28:26.003
You love this door, you
said it was perfect.

28:26.005 --> 28:27.071
- I know.

28:27.073 --> 28:28.706
- I thought it
was creepy, you said no,

28:28.708 --> 28:29.707
he says it's creepy--

28:29.709 --> 28:30.808
- I know.

28:30.810 --> 28:32.943
- You sure you're not
overreacting?

28:34.413 --> 28:36.380
- You always say I'm
overreacting.

28:38.517 --> 28:39.416
- Well.

28:39.418 --> 28:45.289
- Okay, well, he cleared the
house, so maybe we're good.

28:45.558 --> 28:48.592
- I'm sure that did
it, clearing the house.

28:50.930 --> 28:52.996
Honey, I will get to it, I
just can't do it tonight.

28:52.998 --> 28:57.868
- Fine, we'll just keep it
till the weekend and see.

29:00.806 --> 29:05.876
- Maybe on the weekend you
can get a nice beaded curtain.

29:07.379 --> 29:09.680
(laughing)

29:23.596 --> 29:24.428
- [Woman] How can I help you?

29:24.430 --> 29:26.363
- Hi, I'm new to town and--

29:26.365 --> 29:28.532
- And you need a library card.

29:28.534 --> 29:33.604
- No, I mean yes, but,
actually, I'm looking for

29:33.873 --> 29:37.975
reference material for any
local stories or legends about,

29:40.312 --> 29:42.312
about the supernatural stuff.

29:42.314 --> 29:44.982
- Oh, local haunts and ghost
stories?

29:44.984 --> 29:46.717
- Yes, exactly.

29:46.718 --> 29:48.451
- There's a local interest
section, there might be

29:48.454 --> 29:50.420
some books there you'd be
interested in.

29:50.422 --> 29:52.256
Ghost stories,
old haunts or was there

29:52.258 --> 29:54.358
something in particular?

29:54.360 --> 29:56.426
- You know, I don't really
know where to start,

29:56.428 --> 29:58.095
do you have any ideas?

29:58.097 --> 30:01.265
- There are some more recent
things, can still talk about

30:01.267 --> 30:05.035
the haunted bridge down
Morris road, a spooky well

30:05.037 --> 30:08.105
and there is the vanishing
children.

30:09.008 --> 30:10.274
- The children.

30:10.276 --> 30:13.577
- Oh, yeah, for decades,
this town has been known

30:13.579 --> 30:17.881
for children being, well,
taken, come with me.

30:20.152 --> 30:22.886
(ominous music)

30:34.066 --> 30:36.667
That's it, she was the last one.

30:36.669 --> 30:41.238
- Maggie Bradford, this
is over 20 years ago.

30:41.240 --> 30:44.608
- And they stopped after
her, the vanishings,

30:44.610 --> 30:48.579
they go way back before that,
at least a couple a year.

30:48.581 --> 30:51.014
There were some arrests,
but no convictions.

30:51.016 --> 30:53.517
- And no one every found them?

30:53.519 --> 30:55.118
- Not a one.

30:55.120 --> 30:57.855
(ominous music)

31:02.494 --> 31:05.829
- Some decaffeinated
sleepy time tea.

31:11.370 --> 31:12.469
What's going on?

31:16.108 --> 31:19.776
- I went to the library
today to do some research.

31:19.778 --> 31:20.711
- About the door.

31:23.215 --> 31:24.114
- Yeah.

31:27.720 --> 31:28.986
- Did you find anything?

31:30.556 --> 31:32.456
- Yes, some stuff
about missing children,

31:36.562 --> 31:37.945
who were never found.

31:37.946 --> 31:39.329
- You know, every town has
missing children stories.

31:39.331 --> 31:42.833
- This is a lot of children,
over a long time, Red,

31:43.802 --> 31:45.035
it's unnerving.

31:46.205 --> 31:49.806
- Well, you know,
you can get unnerved,

31:49.808 --> 31:53.243
when children are in
danger and especially Kane.

31:55.047 --> 31:58.015
And I think it's because it
was so much work having him.

31:59.685 --> 32:01.084
I mean it wasn't so much work,

32:01.086 --> 32:05.355
but we were very lucky.

32:05.357 --> 32:07.190
- We were so lucky, you know.

32:09.161 --> 32:14.264
- And the stress of moving
and your psychic buddy

32:14.266 --> 32:17.801
throwing fuel on the fire, I
think you're getting caught up

32:17.803 --> 32:19.069
in creepy stories.

32:22.241 --> 32:24.441
How are we supposed to tell
Kane there's no such thing

32:24.443 --> 32:26.643
as ghosts, when mommy's
jumping in shadows?

32:29.682 --> 32:31.214
- Yeah, I know, you're right.

32:37.122 --> 32:39.856
(alarm beeping)

32:46.432 --> 32:47.564
Good morning.

32:52.104 --> 32:55.839
I forgot to set the timer on
the coffee maker last night.

32:55.841 --> 32:57.240
- I did it.

32:57.242 --> 33:01.945
- Oh, my hero, you want eggs?

33:02.848 --> 33:04.915
- I gotta stick
with toast and coffee.

33:06.452 --> 33:10.087
- Yeah, but you like
eggs, I don't mind it.

33:13.225 --> 33:14.124
- My hero.

33:17.930 --> 33:22.699
If you get Kane ready for
school, I'll take him.

33:30.576 --> 33:31.475
Evelyn.

33:33.012 --> 33:33.910
- Yeah?

33:34.880 --> 33:37.414
- [Red] Can you take
a look at this?

33:37.416 --> 33:40.150
(ominous music)

33:50.396 --> 33:53.964
Maybe this weekend
we get a new door.

34:14.719 --> 34:17.454
(ominous music)

35:36.735 --> 35:39.469
(phone ringing)

35:43.375 --> 35:44.274
- Oh, no.

35:45.844 --> 35:49.379
- As you know, this is
not out first incident.

35:50.315 --> 35:53.083
As accommodating
as this school may be,

35:53.085 --> 35:56.853
we have a zero tolerance
policy for violence.

35:56.855 --> 35:58.689
- [Red] We know and--

35:58.690 --> 36:00.524
- [Raleigh] I've talked
to several other families

36:00.526 --> 36:03.260
and while I don't
excuse their behavior.

36:10.169 --> 36:13.403
(children chattering)

36:23.749 --> 36:25.782
- [Evelyn] How can they just
kick him out?

36:25.784 --> 36:26.616
- [Red] It's a private school,

36:26.618 --> 36:27.984
they can do whatever they want.

36:27.986 --> 36:29.753
- [Evelyn] That school was
built for special kids,

36:29.755 --> 36:31.555
kids with needs like Kane's,
to kick him out, it's--

36:31.557 --> 36:34.357
- It's not fair, it's not
right and it's what happened.

36:36.795 --> 36:39.329
On Monday I'll go talk
to the principal Raleigh,

36:39.331 --> 36:41.631
maybe she'll be in a
different frame of mind.

36:42.601 --> 36:45.068
But as it is, we gotta start
looking for a new school.

36:46.171 --> 36:49.039
- I'll call the tutor the
councilor recommended.

36:49.041 --> 36:50.574
Maybe he won't
fall too far behind,

36:50.576 --> 36:51.741
while he's out of class.

36:51.743 --> 36:53.009
- How much does the tutor cost?

36:53.011 --> 36:54.177
- It's not cheap.

36:54.179 --> 36:55.078
- [Red] Great.

36:56.748 --> 37:00.650
- I'll get a job, the
online business can wait.

37:01.620 --> 37:03.954
- It may have to, you
know the contract I signed

37:03.956 --> 37:05.422
with the school about trading
renovations

37:05.424 --> 37:07.857
for Kane's tuition, well,
now, that Kane's no longer

37:07.859 --> 37:12.329
at school I get a cash
payment, a low cash payment.

37:12.331 --> 37:13.663
- How low?

37:13.665 --> 37:14.564
- [Red] Low.

37:15.734 --> 37:18.435
- How are we gonna be
able to pay the bills?

37:18.437 --> 37:19.970
- We'll figure something out.

37:21.907 --> 37:24.574
Important thing is we
get him back at school.

37:25.978 --> 37:27.110
- But how do we even--

37:27.112 --> 37:29.813
- Punish him?

37:29.814 --> 37:32.515
- Do we, I mean those other
kids, those kids push him

37:32.517 --> 37:35.085
and then he's already grounded.

37:35.087 --> 37:37.387
- I'll take him to
work with me tomorrow.

37:37.389 --> 37:39.089
It's Saturday,
nobody will be at school,

37:39.091 --> 37:41.558
he can do his math work
book and his reading.

37:42.361 --> 37:45.495
He stays here, it'll be
too much like vacation.

37:45.497 --> 37:46.329
- You're a good dad.

37:46.331 --> 37:47.330
- You're a great mom.

37:49.534 --> 37:50.967
- We'll figure it out.

37:50.969 --> 37:52.302
- We always do.

38:08.620 --> 38:10.487
- Okay, be good
for your dad today,

38:10.489 --> 38:12.088
don't distract him from work.

38:12.090 --> 38:13.223
- Okay.
- Okay.

38:14.426 --> 38:15.358
Bye.

38:15.360 --> 38:16.359
- Love you.

38:17.429 --> 38:18.995
- Have a good day.

38:21.066 --> 38:23.633
(piano music)

38:36.381 --> 38:39.182
(dramatic music)

39:19.691 --> 39:22.025
(knocking)

39:22.027 --> 39:24.861
(birds chirping)

39:29.901 --> 39:33.670
Hello, my name's Evelyn Eden
and I was just wondering

39:33.672 --> 39:37.140
and I know this sounds
odd, but I was wondering,

39:37.142 --> 39:39.275
if you had any information
about the old house,

39:39.277 --> 39:42.345
that used to be in the
clearing, the one, that burned.

39:42.347 --> 39:43.847
- What about it?

39:43.849 --> 39:45.682
- I was just looking for anyone
with any

39:45.684 --> 39:50.754
information about it, I
wanted to, there was a door.

39:51.423 --> 39:55.058
- You're the one,
who took the door.

39:56.027 --> 39:57.560
- What do you know
about that door?

39:57.562 --> 39:58.461
- Everything.

40:00.799 --> 40:02.499
You made a terrible mistake.

40:06.671 --> 40:08.805
- Okay, eat your lunch,
do your math, read,

40:08.807 --> 40:10.306
no TV, no games, okay?

40:10.308 --> 40:11.508
- Okay.

40:11.509 --> 40:12.709
- I mean it, I'm just
running to the lumber yard

40:12.711 --> 40:14.344
and I'll be right back, lock the
door.

40:14.346 --> 40:16.679
- I know, lock the door, keep my
phone on,

40:16.681 --> 40:19.682
do not open the door
until when you're home.

40:19.684 --> 40:22.185
- You got it, no games.

40:22.187 --> 40:23.219
- [Kane] I know.

40:24.589 --> 40:29.626
- My daughter Maggie vanished,
just like all the others.

40:31.763 --> 40:36.599
No clues, no demands, no leads,
just gone.

40:36.601 --> 40:39.569
- [Evelyn] Maggie, Maggie
Bradford,

40:40.972 --> 40:42.739
your daughter was the last
victim.

40:44.543 --> 40:47.177
- I knew it was that damn house.

40:47.179 --> 40:49.979
(crows chirping)

40:52.250 --> 40:54.484
- Who lived there?

40:54.486 --> 40:55.385
- No one.

40:58.890 --> 41:00.924
House has been
abandoned for years.

41:02.527 --> 41:04.594
But every story
about a missing kid

41:05.464 --> 41:06.796
led up to that house.

41:08.667 --> 41:12.635
I started thinking there's
something wrong with the house,

41:13.538 --> 41:14.537
the house itself.

41:16.074 --> 41:17.941
- The house was
taking the children.

41:19.678 --> 41:22.545
- [Woman] I told her to
stay away from that house,

41:22.547 --> 41:27.617
I knew, knew, I was wrong and
I wasn't gonna let that house

41:30.689 --> 41:31.955
take another child.

41:34.593 --> 41:35.492
- You burned it.

41:37.562 --> 41:39.662
- I took eight gallons of
kerosene

41:45.837 --> 41:49.739
and I burned it to the ground,
all of it.

41:51.409 --> 41:56.446
Except the door,
it wouldn't burn.

41:57.215 --> 41:59.949
(ominous music)

42:24.242 --> 42:27.877
So I took two more gallons
of gas and I lit it up.

42:30.015 --> 42:33.683
But that door wouldn't
burn, so I buried it

42:36.488 --> 42:39.489
and I buried that door
eight feet underground,

42:40.725 --> 42:42.525
and I threw the key in the pond.

42:46.231 --> 42:47.063
- So why was it--

42:47.065 --> 42:48.698
- I went back the next day

42:51.836 --> 42:53.870
and that door was standing in
its place

42:55.540 --> 42:59.375
straight up like an oak,
like it had grown there

42:59.377 --> 43:04.247
out of the ground, key and
lock, so I wrapped it in chains.

43:05.116 --> 43:09.786
And I fastened that key in the
lock, and I left it to rot.

43:11.623 --> 43:13.856
- And the children stopped
vanishing.

43:13.858 --> 43:14.958
- For 20 years,

43:16.428 --> 43:18.595
but then you took the door.

43:26.571 --> 43:27.837
- We took off the chain.

43:30.942 --> 43:33.509
- You let it loose, Ms. Eden.

43:33.511 --> 43:36.245
- What is it, Missis Bradford,
what is behind that door?

43:36.247 --> 43:40.883
- I don't know,
but it takes children

43:42.787 --> 43:44.554
and it doesn't give them back.

43:47.826 --> 43:49.092
I don't know what it is,

43:52.530 --> 43:56.099
but it's a very bad thing.

43:56.101 --> 43:58.835
(phone ringing)

44:01.206 --> 44:04.040
- I need to go, thank you.

44:04.042 --> 44:06.509
- [Ms. Bradford] Get rid
of that door, Ms. Eden.

44:21.893 --> 44:24.894
- Kane, Kane, honey,
open the door.

44:26.831 --> 44:27.930
(knocking)

44:27.932 --> 44:29.098
Kane, honey, open the door.

44:29.100 --> 44:29.999
- What's going on?

44:30.001 --> 44:31.634
- [Evelyn] Kane!

